<item>
            <title>[HBASE-23590] Update maxStoreFileRefCount to maxCompactedStoreFileRefCount</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-23590</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per discussion on&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-23349&quot; title=&quot;Low refCount preventing archival of compacted away files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-23349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-23349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, RegionsRecoveryChore should use max refCount on compacted away store files and not on new store files to determine when to reopen the region. Although work on&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-23349&quot; title=&quot;Low refCount preventing archival of compacted away files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-23349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-23349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;is in progress, we need to at least update the metric to get the desired refCount i.e. max refCount among all compacted away store files for a given region.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13275263">HBASE-23590</key>
            <summary>Update maxStoreFileRefCount to maxCompactedStoreFileRefCount</summary>
