                            <comment id="17001858" author="vjasani" created="Sun, 22 Dec 2019 10:32:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apurtell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apurtell&quot;&gt;apurtell&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-22460&quot; title=&quot;Reopen a region if store reader references may have leaked&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-22460&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-22460&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;has not yet landed to any releases (2.3.0/1.6.1) and now we know that the refCounts that we had taken into consideration are not the correct ones, (we calculate refCount of current store files instead of compacted away store files) could you please review this patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry for being late on this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While work on&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-23349&quot; title=&quot;Low refCount preventing archival of compacted away files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-23349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-23349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;is still in progress(low no of refCounts), with this Jira, we can ensure that at least we can deal with abnormally high no of refCounts(~1k) preventing archival of compacted store files(the bug fix associated with it). Will attach branch-1 backport to this Jira once the patch looks good to you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
